channel.title: A good source
channel.description: Hey guys, I am looking for a good, clean, stable 317 PI source. I have been trying to learn more Java and I think I have done somewhat good so far.. I am hoping to make a new server called Valacity but I have no idea what source to use! All these dspk's are driving me insane! I go in server downloads and all the PI's I see are dspk.. I really need a source that ISN'T dspk and that is very stable and clean. If you have a suggestion please comment. :)

item.title: A good source
item.dc:creator: @Vexillum Vexillum
item.description:
@Vexillum wrote:

Sagi:

Try my source, it is not dspk and stable enough: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,465068.0.html

I may use your source.

[quote=“dain bramage, post:8, topic:404062”]If you’re serious about learning java and making a respectable server, try RuneSource, or any of these:
http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,427654.0.html[/quote]

I am 100% serious I am reading this tutorial atm: http://www.optimalbyte.com/forum/index.php?topic=343.0

And I am following a youtube playlist on how to learn Java. I’m about half way through the tutorial atm and after that I will watch the youtube vids and practice some Java in eclipse.
